              <p class="service-left">
                This early intervention program provides child abuse education to elementary school children. 
                The goal of this program is to educate young children about child abuse, at their level of understanding, utilizing methods such as coloring book exercises, games and the “Safety Bear” to learn the difference between “good” and “bad” touches, 
                which secrets are safe to keep and which are not, and when an adult or older child is being inappropriate, and most importantly 
                –The three Safety Bear Rules (NO, GO, and TELL).
              </p>
              
