                Prevention and Early Intervention (PEI) programs are utilized to meet the needs of those clients experiencing their first interaction with the mental health system who can benefit from short term treatment. 
                The goal of our PEI programs is to quickly meet the needs of the family and return the family to their previous level of functioning as soon as possible, preventing the need for more intensive services in the future. 
                Our PEI program utilizes five Evidence Based Practices. These practices include Trauma-focused Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Individual Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Reflective Parenting Program, Parent Child Interactive Therapy, and Managing and Adapting Practices. 
